# ── JobEarly Environment Variables ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values.
# Never commit your actual .env file to git.

# ── Gmail / Google OAuth ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required for the Outreach Gmail integration.
#
# Step-by-step setup:
# 1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 2. Create a new project (or select an existing one)
# 3. Enable the Gmail API:
#    APIs & Services → Library → search "Gmail API" → Enable
# 4. Create OAuth 2.0 credentials:
#    APIs & Services → Credentials → Create Credentials → OAuth client ID
#    - Application type: Web application
#    - Name: JobEarly (or anything)
#    - Authorised JavaScript origins: http://localhost:5173
#    - Authorised redirect URIs: http://localhost:5173
#    Click Create → copy the Client ID
# 5. Configure OAuth consent screen:
#    APIs & Services → OAuth consent screen
#    - User type: External
#    - App name: JobEarly
#    - Add scopes: Gmail API (gmail.readonly, gmail.send, gmail.modify)
#    - Add yourself as a test user (your Gmail address)
# 6. Paste the Client ID below:

VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id-here.apps.googleusercontent.com

# Note: In development the OAuth popup works on http://localhost:5173
# For production deployment, add your production domain to Authorised JavaScript origins.
